                <p>After our first itteration of the project, we had a much better grasp at how this app needed to be structured. Our first approach used a simple .json file which contained the collected mountain data. The .json was manually inputted as a mock pull from an API for mountain weather conditions. We used jQuery to then collect and dislay the information through the front-end of the site. 
                <p>The next iteration of the site is being built using a stack of SASS, jQuery, and .Backbone with the help of a python and jango back-en. Below are the newest front-end high-fidelity mockups.</p>
